The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Sept. 8: Tata Industries has hiked its stake in two group firms  Tata Motors and Tata Power  through open market transactions worth Rs 700 crore. The Tata group firm has increased its holding in Tata Motors by an additional 0.92 per cent and in Tata Power by a further 0.71 per cent, data available with the Bombay Stock Exchange showed. Tata Industries bought these shares from another group firm Tata Steel.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 8: The government is issuing showcause notices to Tata Steel, NTPC, ArcelorMittal and 78 other companies, who are sitting on captive coal and lignite reserves, to know why they failed to develop these blocks within the stipulated time frame. After reviewing their responses, we will decide on de-allocation of the blocks, coal minister Sriprakash Jaiswal said.                             
	 New York, Sept. 8: Gold today traded near a record level as investors sought an alternative to equities and a protection of wealth. Gold added $3.70, or 0.3 per cent, to $1,263 an ounce on the Comex in New York, close to its highest level of $1,265.30 set on June 28.
                                                                                                                          
